The '''Gugang Lake''' ({{zh|c=古崗湖|p=Gǔgǎng Hú}} is a natural [[lake]] in [[Jincheng, Kinmen|Jincheng Township]], [[Kinmen County]], [[Taiwan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tour.kinmen.gov.tw/english/spot_detail.aspx?sn=1301&n=10509 |title=Welcome~~ Kinmen Classic Travel-Jincheng Town |publisher=Tour.kinmen.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

==Geology==
The lake is surrounded by hills and [[willows]] growing on its shore.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://web.kinmen.gov.tw/Layout/sub_D/AllInOne_en_Show.aspx?path=7054&guid=6d73dfd6-3183-46ff-81f9-6f4ecb348d85&lang=en-us|title=Gugang Lake|publisher=}}</ref>

==Ecology==
The lake is the habitat for aquatic birds, especially the European hoopoes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://kinmen.travel/en/travel/attraction/1301|date=9 November 2018|title=Gugang Lake Scenic Area (Gugang Tower and Gugang Lake)|website=Classic Kinmen Travel|accessdate=29 November 2018}}</ref>

==Features==
The lake features the Gugang Pavilion which was built in 1964 by Zhuang Wu-nan from [[Tamsui]], [[Taipei]]. The pavilion is 16 meters in height.<ref>{{cite web|author=Robb&#39;s Ramblings &amp; Resources |url=http://robbsramblings.blogspot.com/2011/10/gugang-tower-on-kinmen-island.html |title=Robbs Ramblings: Gugang Tower on Kinmen Island |publisher=Robbsramblings.blogspot.com |date=2011-10-01 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref>

